description: As the sole, unharmed survivor of the attack on his precinct, Detective Basil follows left behind clues that leads to a clandestine meeting with a Grandma!? What can she possibly know about the villainous CrossStar? Meanwhile CrossStar infiltrates a hidden terrorist camp where he confronts the notorious Mr. Marble.

Inspired by the beloved story by Antoine Saint-Exupry, The Little Prince series was developed by prestigious French publisher Glenat with the guidance of the author's estate. The universe is in danger: the stars are going out one by one along the path of the Serpent. The Little Prince, determined not to let evil rule the galaxy, leaves his asteroid and his beloved Rose on a monumental quest. Accompanied by this faithful friend Fox, he will discover vast worlds set off kilter by strange rules and dangerous strife and will use his extraordinary gifts to help bring balance to each planet.
name: Book Three: The Planet Of Music

description: The Little Prince, determined not to let evil rule the galaxy, leaves his asteroid and his beloved Rose on a monumental quest. Accompanied by this faithful friend Fox, he will discover vast worlds set off kilter by strange rules and dangerous strife and will use his extraordinary gifts to help bring balance to each planet. Characters in this graphic novel series have been reimagined in new adventures while maintaining the essential mood and spirit of the classic original by Antoine Saint-Exupry.
name: Book 4: The Planet Of Jade

description: The battlelines are drawn. With each passing hour, the sorcerer Kulan Gath uses the Mayan 2012 doomsday prophecy to push the world closer to destruction. But his sworn enemy Red Sonja followed him through time itself, and has now gathered a team of allies to oppose Gath and his army of the dead. Joined by Vampirella, Dracula, Pantha, Herbert West the Reanimator and many more, Sonja has sworn to stop Gath, even if the cost is her own soul. Dynamite's biggest crossover ever rolls on, masterminded by writer Ron Marz, with artist Walter Geovani doing the best work of his career!
name: Book Three

description:
This issue contains 3 complete stories:

Operazione di recupero

Branko is sent on a mission to find a spy-drone that crashed in the middle of a tropical forest. This seemingly easy task will put him face to face with a forgotten part of his past...

Madre vendetta

A woman is threatening to blow up a space station, specialized in entertainment and gambling. Hers is not just a terrorist attack. But what’s her secret? Only May Frayn, armed with her compassion, will be able to find out in time!

Il culto della follia

In the underground maze of the ancient Babylon, a people of alien being is developing its own civilization, under the careful watch of human observers. May is sent there for an inspection, but she soon realizes something’s wrong. Why the dwellers of that underground world appear to be terrorized by a scary idol who looks like a robot? And why are Kay and a journalist friend of May’s haunted by terrifying visions?
name: Operazione di recupero

description: It is the Mexican Day of the Dead, and Lieutenant Santos has a nasty surprise for the people of Big Star City.
name: Día De Los Muertos

description: In this issue we are introduced to Scratch, our protagonist and "the 22nd Century's Most Misunderstood Mass Murderer".
name: "...and they shall know my name by the trail of dead..."

description:
Operazione Viper

A disgusting Temsek experiment on a Caribbean island... In the middle of a hurricane, Harlan and Kurjak, on board of a cargo ship, will have to fight the fury of the elements and the horrors unleashed by ”Operation Viper”!

Urla dal profondo

When the divers of the salvage tug “Orion” find the wreck of the “Graceland”, a ship of the Puritan Pilgrims sunk in the 17th century, the horror begins! The quiet hamlet of Halleck Island is threatened by dark forces and only Harlan and the local Marshall find the strenght to fight against an ancient curse!

L'essenza della follia

Grasse is a French town renowned for its perfume makers... One of them, the amiable Louis, is suffering for a strange amnesia and bizarre visions haunt him. Two demonic persons want the recipe of a dangerous perfume from Louis, following the orders of General Zafon, of the Hell Army...
name: Operazione Viper

description: Wizards of the moon called Loam are desperate to rid themselves of an eldritch djinn threatening their peaceful existence. They are so desperate, in fact, that they are willing to trick one god and kidnap another in order to solicite their assistance. Isis and 10th Muse are thrust together and are forced to make a choice with the fate of an entire society hanging in the balance.

Sent by the Wizard to Makeda Red in order to dispatch a evil Djinn, Isis and 10th Muse are greeted by an army of crazed, hungry Demon Apes. The heroes fight their way to the palace of the Djinn only to discover that the evil they were sent to destroy is in fact the wizard's aged uncle, the man whose magic has kept in check the galactic ambitions of a treacherous nephew!

This Library Marvel includes an important moment in the life of Daredevil. Apparently, the secret identity of Matt Murdock is in danger. Both his partner, Foggy Nelson, as his secretary, Karen Page, suspect that he could actually be the masked hero who wanders New York. To avoid this uncomfortable situation, Matt Murdock decides to "make" his "twin brother". Obviously, this acontecimeinto cause a number of unexpected situations.

Also, this volume of Library Marvel: Daredevil, also very important editorial level, since in his comic-book pages includes the Man Without Fear never before been published in Spain.
name: ¡El trihombre vive!

description:
This volume includes Marvel Library, in its first pages, the No. 29 USA of Daredevil, a comic book that has never before been published in Spain. But the highlight of this volume is in a storyline where Daredevil faces Mr. Hyde and Cobra, a couple of villains of great importance in early issues of the Library Marvel: Thor.

In conclusion, this volume also includes the first Annual Daredevil. It is a long story in which the Man Without Fear faces the Emissaries of Evil, a group composed of Electro, the Matador, the mosquito, the Gladiator and the Jumping Frog.
name: ¡Desemascarado!

description:
So far it has been quite normal that some of the comics-books USA included in previous volumes in this series show the appearance of another character from the Marvel Universe. This time, the components of the Fantastic 4 appear in much of the USA comics included in this volume. This is because Stan Lee and Gene Colan us a story line, consisting of two consecutive stories where villains Daredevil faces Marvel caracteríticos Quartet (the Trapper and Dr. Doom).

Thus. this volume might well be described as a "Special Fantastic 4" Library Marvel: Daredevil.
name: ¡Aplastar a un escarabajo!

description:
One of the bizarre ideas of Stan Lee was the creation of Mike Murdock, the "twin" of Matt Murdock. The aim of this new character ghost was to divert attention from Karen Page and Foggy Nelson, so that none of them could come to discover the true identity of Daredevil.

However, the permanence of this new identity also led to some problems. As a result, Stan Lee decided to end Mike Murdock, which takes place on the first pages of this volume of Library Marvel.

Likewise, this issue also includes the first aparivión Jester, one of the major villains of the Man Without Fear, and a mythical battle between Captain America and Daredevil.
name: ¡El heroe caido!

description:
This volume of Library Marvel: Daredevil features the work of two great artists. One of them, of course, is always excellent Gene Colan. The other is Barry Windsor-Smith, who draws a series of three comic books. This is one of his early work for Marvel.

In addition, this volume also includes No. 47 USA Daredevil, whose script by Stan Lee is regarded as one of his best works. This is a comic that even was part of the original edition of the book Son of Origins. Lee himself said the following regarding the comic: "I admit it ... I was really trying to say something with this story, and put it delicately. But read it for yourselves, and you will see what I mean.".
name: ¡Hermano toma mi mano!

description:
In this issue of Library Marvel takes place a very special event, an event closely related to the private life of Daredevil.

Since the start of this series, Matt Murdock has tried to keep secret life as masked hero, especially to his partner, Foggy Nelson, and Secretary of both Karen Page. However, his continuing adventures came to jeopardize his secret to such an extent that even decided to establish the identity of his "twin brother", Mike Murdock to coworkers thought the latter was really Daredevil.

However, the new developments that have taken place are responsible for the Man Without Fear is seen in the need to reveal his secret identity ...
name: ¡Llamadle... Mr. Miedo!

description:
Marvel Library This volume is divided into two distinct parts.

In the first one, Daredevil faces a deadly trio of villains consisting of the Fool, Cobra and Mr. Hyde. And then measure its strength against himself Nighthawk (who was the mysterious component Squadron Sinister) and against the Gladiator (one of his most dangerous enemies).

In the second part of the volume, Matt Murdock travels to Los Angeles to follow in the footsteps of Karen Page (who is touted his new career as an actress). Once in California, Daredevil faces a new series of new threats, which is another of his classic enemies: the Zancudo.
name: ¡Atrapado ... por el frio letal!

description:
When he began his stage in this collection, Roy Thomas wrote a story in which Daredevil was helped by the Black Panther. The idea of uniting the fates of both characters was successful ...

Now, just when this guionita ends its first phase in this title, restates something very similar. This time, Thomas wrote a number USA (69) where the Man Without Fear and the King of Wakanda form a team-up to face a gang of underworld ...

And at the end of this volume of Marvel library, we have a full-fledged crossover that sets a cross between collections Daredevil and Iron Man is a story which will also Nick Fury and Madame Masque. They will face the Zodiac and discover the secret of a group like this so enigmatic.
name: ¡Una vida en peligro!

description:
With the advent of the '70s, the writer of Daredevil post, changed hands, from Roy Thomas Gerry Conway.

The new writer quickly demonstrated his knowledge of the art of the crossover, making the stories in the collection were crossed with other Marvel Universe titles. In this volume in particular, the creative team formed by Gerry Conway and Gene Colan developed a unique crossover between Daredevil and Namor, with Spiderman as essential nexus.

In addition, this volume also includes Marvel Library USA number which hosted the arrival of a very special guest character: the Black Widow, who will form tandem with the Man Without Fear in the coming months.
name: ¡Asi cabalga el fantasma de ... El Condor!

description:
Finally the time has come that many readers were waiting, from this volume of Library Marvel: Daredevil, the mysterious Black Widow becomes the great co-star of the collection. In fact (and to be fair), the title should change in the coming months to adopt the Library Marvel: Daredevil / Black Widow.

So, in this volume we find that this new tandem of heroes will face two legendary villains such as the Scorpion and Mr. Hyde, which hides an important secret inside.

Then Daredevil and Black Widow will face off with the Gladiator, Electro, Ox and the Purple Man through four stories autoconclusivas.
name: ¡Y ahora llega ... el Escorpion!

description:
This volume of Marvel Library contains a series of seven issues of Daredevil USA, all made by the same creative team: Gerry Conway (dashes), Gene Colan (pencil drawings) and Tom Palmer (inks).

A plot level, this volume begins with the conclusion of a saga in which Daredevil and Black Widow singular face the Purple Man (supported by his band) and Electro, the great master of electricity.

Just then takes place the return of one of the villains most characteristic of this collection, it's Mr. Fear, an entity that refuses to disappear from the life of the Man Without Fear. In this story, also will show details of the origin of the Black Widow.
name: ¡Crisis!

description:
This volume begins with the Library Marvel expected conclusion of the story begun last month with the Man Toro as great villain.

Just after starting a storyline in which takes place the first appearance of a number of new villains very singular nature. However, the highlight of this volume comes next, this is a great crossover between Daredevil / Black Widow and the Avengers, where they all join forces to successfully confront a resurgent Magneto.

In addition, this volume also includes the 100th USA of Man without Fear, which means the end of the long stage drawn by Gene Colan.
name: ¡La Viuda Negra te lo hara pagar!

description:
On an artistic level, this volume of Marvel Library includes a transition period going from the stage to Gene Colan new era characterized by Bob Brown, an artist in the collection of Daredevil made ​​his most important work in the House of ideas.

In addition, this volume includes the first work of Chris Claremont for Marvel. This is the talks of # 102 USA title of The Man Without Fear.

In terms of plot is important to note that some of the stories in this volume connect with Thanos War (see Library Marvel: Captain Marvel). Hence the appearance occurs Moondragon and Captain Marvel himself.
name: ¡El Zancudo acecha la ciudad!

description:
Marvel Library This volume devotes half of its content to a great story line (the Black Spectrum Saga) in which Daredevil and Black Widow and the chuck face Nekra. It also involved as Shanna the She-Devil characters and the Thing. Hence, in the first pages include No. 2 Marvel Two In One, the collection dedicated to presenting the team-up's of the Thing with other characters in the Marvel Universe.

Then Daredevil will meet with one of their classic enemies: the Gladiator. This story also appears the Man-Thing, one of the most strange and mysterious of the House of Ideas.

In the pages of this volume takes place the return of another typical villain in this collection: the Owl.
name: ¡Dentro de Espectro Negro!

description:
This volume begins with Marvel Library concluded the adventure which has taken place in the return of the Owl, one of the oldest and most characteristic enemies of Daredevil.

And just then, a new encounter: this time the Man Without Fear crossed again to Master Track and colorful Circus of Crime (which just entered a new and miterioso component).

Anyway, the highlight of this volume is the series of four numbers USA where Daredevil and Black Widow Hydra face. This is a great story line where we will also (obviously) Nick Fury and his SHIELD agents.
name: ¡Pesadilla!

description:
This volume of Library Marvel: Daredevil contains an interesting set of numbers drawn by Bob Brown and Klaus Janson, an artistic team of first line that prints its seal of quality to the adventures of the Man Without Fear.

Also takes place in its pages the arrival of Marv Wolfman, who occupy positions of writer and editor of the title. His role com head of Daredevil's adventures will be crucial, since he will be the major driver of storylines and new characters like Heather Glenn and Bullseye.

The latter is one of the major villains in the history of the Man Without Fear, whose first appearance occurs in the last two numbers of this volume USA.
name: ¡La venganza de Cabeza de Cobre!

description:
This volume includes several Marvel Boblioteca really interesting content.

In its opening pages, where we found a number takes place USA team-up (as fun as unusual) and Daredevil ... Uri Geller, the famous mentalist who surprised half the world (including Spain) in the mid-70s.

It then presents a unique crossover between collections of Man Without Fear and Ghost Rider, drawn by John Byrne (this was one of his first works for the House of Ideas).

Finally, this volume includes the Annual Daredevil # 4, which remained unpublished in Spain. In this Annual, also featuring characters such as Namor and Black Panther.
name: Onda Mental y su temible ¡Tanque pensante!

description:
This volume of Library Marvel: Daredevil begins with two numbers drawn by Sal Buscema USA. The second one (inked by Klaus Janson) is one of those comics that are not easily forgotten.

Just then return occurs Bullseye, The Owl and the Man Toro duo Cobra and Mr. Hyde.

Then. This volume includes a new confrontation between Daredevil and Bullseye, already emerging as one of the greatest opponents of the Man Without Fear. The story is titled Duel!, Which gives an idea of ​​its contents.

In its final pages, this volume presents an untold story in Spain, where Hawkeye and Two-Gun Kid are the Purple Man.
name: Una noche en la vida ...

description:
This is the last issue of Library Marvel: Daredevil. In the first two chapters, the Man Without Fear will find the Purple Man and Death Lurker, a couple of dangerous villains who have a strong element throughout this volume.

At No. 150 USA takes place the first appearance of Paladin, hire a hero whose path crosses several times with Daredevil. Just then, the Man Without Fear will face Mr.Hyde, Cobra, the Fool and the Gladiator ... but all at once!.

And, in the final pages of the last volume includes an entirely Daredevil story drawn by Steve Ditko.
name: ¡Punto de ruptura!

description: Contains : X-Men (2010) #22,23 - Uncanny X-Force (2010) #18,19 - Astonishing X-Men (2004) #48
name: Rapprochements

description: Contains : X-Men (2010) #24,25 - Uncanny X-Force (2010) #19.1,20 - Astonishing X-Men (2004) #49
name: Le retour des Fantômes

description: Contains : New Mutants (2009) #33-37 - X-Men: To Serve and Protect (2011)# 03 (4rd story) … And You’ll Miss It
Contains : Magneto: Not A Hero (2011) #01-04 - X-Men: To Serve and Protect (2011)# 02 (2rd story)
Contains : X-Factor (2006) #220 - 224

Marc Saunders is the best secret agent the United States has ever seen. And...oh...he has super powers. But shh, that's a secret. However, something even powerful than Marc has appeared. Something that Marc must stop before the United States - and the world - is destroyed!

This first issue of Daredevil Collectible ends with the first comic book drawn by Frank Miller, which will mark the beginning of one of the most important stages in the history of man without fear. A stage will mark a before and after in the original series.

The next volume will begin with a story cycle clearly divided into two parts. In the first, an anonymous man (at least initially) hires a band of gangsters to end the life of Daredevil. The second part will take place and the expected return of villain considered more important in this series. We refer, of course, Bullseye, who can turn any object into a deadly weapon.

In the last few pages we will see a unique confrontation between man and the land without fear most powerful ...
name: ¿El hombre sin miedo?

description:
Daredevil start the third issue of this collectible ... bedridden in a hospital. His "encounter" with Hulk ja been fighting like a real steamroller and the result is as logical as devastating.

The Man Without Fear will be visited by some of the most important heroes of the Marvel Universe New York ... But also a legendary journalist, Ben Urich, who narrate the origin of Daredevil. Becoming a supervillain closely related to Spiderman: Dr Octopus. And we will meet right after the return of the Gladiator and the first appearance of Macero.

But there is no doubt that the most important of the next issue will be held in the last pages. They ... Man without fear Elektra will find probably the most important anti-heroine of the 80s Marvel.
name: Marcado por la muerte

description:
This volume recreates a pivotal moment in the life of Matt Murdock, the stage of his life when he met Elektra ... and that will lead, in the next issue, in the first story of Murdock as masked hero.

Just then there will be another appearance of Bullseye. But this time the dangerous villain appears mired in madness. For some unknown reason does nothing to see people dressed as Daredevil everywhere, and that makes it a real bomb ...

But the highlight of the next issue has a name: Kingpin. After a long season, the former great New York crime boss has decided to return to the Big Apple to regain his throne.

And will do anything to achieve their goal ...
name: Elektra

description: The flying legend of the Golden Age is back in action in post-war Tokyo! Davy Nelson, the kid fighting ace of World War II, is embroiled in a conspiracy to return Japan to the horrors of the past under the rule of a mad shogun! Birdy, Airboy's miracle plane, is in the hands of the bad guys, and the Yakuza and an army of robotic killers stand in the way of a reunion!

On the last page of this volume Daredevil Any thoughts inexorably destined to certain death. Although ... as everyone imagines, our hero would be saved ...

This is precisely the story that begins the next issue of this collectable, a number where we will have the presence of the two major opponents of Man without Fear: Bullseye and Kingpin. Bullseye star in one of the most violent and decisive confrontation with Daredevil. But if each individually represents a significant hazard, together can become almost insurmountable threat ...

Later again another great characters in this series: Elektra. This return will be part of a story where a group of ninjas known as murderers-Hand-try to kill a New York lawyer ...
name: En las garras de Kingpin

description:
It's a miracle that astro-nots Krunk and Quinn have managed to stay out of the joint this long, but their luck has run out. Now residents of Honest Abe's Penitentiary, Krunk and Quinn have to find a way out or learn to make new friends (if you know what I mean). Luckily, Krunk's big, bad mom ain't about to let her baby boy go punk, and woe be to he who gets in her way . . . or who doesn't. Meanwhile, vengeful space-hottie Neoki realizes that to get back her priceless idol, she's going to need the key around Quinn's neck-and she's going to have to get it before the time bomb around his neck goes boom!

Relentlessly marching forward in their quest to embarrass their families, Zach Howard (Shaun of the Dead) and Sean Murphy (Scarecrow: Year One; Off Road), with screenwriter Reed Buccholz, have created Outer Orbit, an "epic" science-fiction/action-comedy/adjective-noun forged from equal parts stupidity, idiocy, and imbecility. And in case you were wondering, yes, sheep are involved.

Due to an unexpected accident, Matt Murdock lost his legendary sense of radar, and his role as a crime fighter has clearly been compromised. Will it take long to regain his power?

All this and we'll know more in the next issue, we will show a dramatic showdown between Elektra and a kind of super-ninja by the name of Kirigi.

In addition, Matt Murdock will meet a key figure from his past. This is someone who had not seen for many years and he will remember when he suffered the accident that left him blind, the sameness time, was endowed with great powers.

Yet another important appearance: Powerman and Iron Fist, one of the most famous couples in the Marvel Universe of the 80s.
name: Guerra de bandas
